h2.div: SNHU preparing weekend meal packs for Manchester Students - See below

div.p: Weekend meal package distribution will continue on Saturday mornings. All meals are donated and prepared by Southern New Hampshire University, and handed out by volunteers. The schedule for this weekend is below.

ul.li: Memorial High School, 1 Crusader Way: 9:30-11:30 am
Manchester Police Athletic League, 409 Beech St.: 9:30-11:30 am
Parkside Middle School, 75 Parkside Ave.: 9:30-11:30 am
Smyth Road School, 245 Bruce Road: 9:30-10 am
Crystal Lake Park, 679 Bodwell Road: 10:30-11 am

div.p: Please remember social distancing – when waiting for meal pickup, it’s very important to make sure you’re standing 6 feet away from others. When picking up food, you may want to bring a bag to more easily transport food home. Also, make sure to properly store food.

div.small: MSD is actively working to increase the accessibility and usability of its website. If you wish to report an issue or suggestion related to the accessibility of any content on our website, please use the feedback link on the home page.
It is the policy of the Manchester Board of School Committee, in its actions, and those of its employees, that there shall be no

or sexual orientation for employment in, or operation and administration of any program or activity in the Manchester School
District. The Title IX Coordinator is Sherri Nichols for staff; the 504 and Title IX Coordinator is Mary Steady for students.
Please see above for contact information.
